[h1]GK Ethics & Civics[/h1]

A governance and economics overhaul. New ethics, new civics, new starts.

[h2]Ethics[/h2]

One new axis alongside the vanilla ones, no vanilla ethics are removed.

[b]Individualist[/b]: Private ownership, free enterprise, merit-based hierarchy.
+10% Ruler Bonus Workforce, -5% Trade Fee (doubled at Fanatic).
Unlocks Stratified Economy.

[b]Collectivist[/b]: Collective ownership, shared prosperity, worker solidarity.
-10% Amenities Usage, -10% Housing Usage, +5% Worker Production (doubled at Fanatic).
Unlocks Utopian Abundance.

Each ethic has a full faction with unique demands tied to economic policy, diplomacy, and government.

[b]Authoritarian[/b]: (reworked) Boosts enforcer efficiency instead of generic worker output.
+10% Enforcer Jobs Bonus Workforce (doubled at Fanatic).

[h2]Civics[/h2]

All civics have variants for standard empires, megacorps, hive minds, and machine intelligences where applicable.

[b]Centralized State[/b]: Concentrate power and resources in your capital at the expense of the periphery. Ruler jobs scale with capital tier.

[b]Penal Colonies[/b]: Put your criminals to work. Start with Penal Colonies technology and gain enforcers that produce unity.

[b]Leisure Society[/b]: Build a culture of comfort and recreation. Start with Resort Colonies technology and gain entertainers that produce unity.

[h2]Home System Starts[/h2]
[list]
[*] [b]Ruined Habitat[/b]:Trinary system with the remnants of a prior civilization and a ruined habitat megastructure. Habitat tech available from game start. No guaranteed habitable planets
[*] [b]Lunar Colony[/b]: Large capital world with a pre-colonized habitable moon. No guaranteed habitable planets
[*] [b]Titanic Homeworld[/b]: Oversized, resource-rich homeworld in a system of massive celestial bodies. No guaranteed habitable planets
[/list]